<br>
I know who many of the mover-and-shaker Enchanters, Druids, etc are in my area.  I know who are clerics I deal and group with regularly.<br>
<br>
I've never had trouble with my /LFG flag on finding a workable group.  With a few well-placed /shouts, I typically get one or two /tells within minutes.<br>
<br>
And for places I know are going to be problems pulling a group together once I'm there, like Lesser Faydark, I'll get the group together in a city, like Kelethin, first.  Not only does this encourage social behavior, but it's also somewhat more realistic.<br>
<br>
Sorry, I just don't buy that this is as big a problem as some people want to make it out to be.  That's not been my experience, and there a ton of ways to &quot;work around&quot; it that are easy and well within the capabilities of any character.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, the argument doesn't hold water on its own merits.  If there are so few people in these zones that it's hard to find group-mates, then it shouldn't take long to send a /tell to each of the people in the zone asking them if they want to group and what their class/level is.  If, on the other hand, there are a lot of people in the zone, then finding a group really isn't a problem at all, as long as you put yourself out as looking for one.<br>
<br>
